      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so im working on this script to process some huge csv files with pandas but im getting a MemoryError every time i run it. i think it might be because of how i'm loading the data. can u explain the main difference between using a list comprehension vs a generator function when im trying to loop through these rows? like which one is better for keeping memory usage low?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A list comprehension builds the entire list in memory at once, which is great for small datasets but will cause a `MemoryError` with huge CSVs. A generator function, on the other hand, yields one item at a time as you iterate over it, meaning it only keeps one row in memory at any given moment. For your massive CSV files, using a generator function is significantly better for keeping memory usage low. You can often achieve this by using the `chunksize` parameter when reading the CSV with pandas.",
