      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so if i use the chunksize thing, it should stop the error, right? i'm also seeing some weird spikes in memory usage even when i'm not doing much, almost like the memory is being eaten up by something in the background or like something is just constantly taking it. how do i figure out if i have a memory leak in my code vs just a heavy process?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If you use `chunksize`, it should prevent the initial loading error by processing the data piece by piece. To check for a memory leak versus a heavy process, you need profiling tools. You can use memory profilers like `memory_profiler` in Python to track exactly which lines of your code are consuming the most memory over time. If the memory usage continuously climbs without ever returning to a baseline, that strongly suggests a leak, not just a heavy, temporary process.",
      "source": "target",
